[SN]TITLE[SN]
Hayden White: Peterborough United boss Grant McCann makes first signing

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Newly-appointed Peterborough boss Grant McCann has made Bolton Wanderers full-back Hayden White his first signing.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 21-year-old, who made 29 league appearances on loan at Blackpool this season, joins Posh on a two-year deal.
White, who was recently released by Bolton, was in the Seasiders team that lost their last game of the season 5-1 at Peterborough.
His arrival comes on the same day that McCann was appointed as full-time manager on a four-year deal.
